    .panel-body
      In this section we discover the main structure of the Stoic Compass: the subdivision of the quadrant in three Disciplines. In the Overview we make a reconnaissance flight over the whole quadrant, showing the general map of the Disciplines and giving a very short description of them.
      %br The following chapters explore the single Disciplines in depth and explain how they are related to Theory and Exercises.
      %br Numerous Meditations from Marcus Aurelius will help the reader to understand how Marcus used the Disciplines to structure his philosophical Practice.
      %br Many Exercises are proposed for every Discipline and permit to put in practice what we have just learned.
