            #collapseInnerTwo3.panel-collapse.collapse
              .panel-body.tab_over
                The Discipline of Assent corresponds to the activity of judgement, i.e., it regards the things that are in our power. The Practice of this Discipline permits the Stoic to free herself from false beliefs and contradictory judgements, it restores and develops the power of the mind, protects the boundaries of the inner Citadel and offers protection and recovery in troubled times.
                It addresses our relationship with human reason and its internal laws.
